This things downloads the list of channels on irc.freenode.net:

    input | sic -h irc.freenode.net -n $nick | tee list | grep --line-buffered "End of /LIST" | kill-children-on-input $$

Sorts and formats them:

    sort -rg "-t$(echo -e '\t')" -k2,2 -k1,1 | \
        awk '{ print $0; if (NR % 5 == 4) { printf "\n" } }'

So that you can read it nicely

    #ubuntu	1714	Official Ubuntu Support Channel | IRC Guidelines: http://ubottu.com/y/gl | IRC info: http://ubottu.com/y/irc | Pastes to http://paste.ubuntu.com/ | Download: http://ubottu.com/y/dl | Currently supported: 10.04 LTS (server), 12.04 LTS, 14.04 LTS, 14.10
    #archlinux	1704	Welcome to Arch Linux World Domination, Inc. <> Read or die: https://bbs.archlinux.org/viewtopic.php?id=57205 <+> pacman 4.2 in [core], don't forget to rebuild/fix/update your aur helper which depends on libalpm (yaourt, cower). Asking questions without reading the topic will get you a kick.
    ##linux	1673	Forums is back in testing http://forums.linuxassist.net | Channel website: http://www.linuxassist.net | Pastebin: http://paste.linuxassist.net | Spammers or trolls? use !ops <troll's nick> <reason>". | For op assistance, join ##linux-ops | Feel at home and enjoy your stay
